# GitHub push cadence

While the user is actively working on this project in a session:

- About once per hour of sustained implementation (or before ending a long session), remind them to commit and push to GitHub if there are unpushed changes.
- Keep the reminder brief: check `git status`, commit meaningful chunks, push to `origin`.
- Do not commit or push unless the user asks; only remind.
- Never commit `.env` files or other secrets.

Remote: `https://github.com/SscottK/esports-team-tracker-v3.git` on branch `main`.
